Ogun State Governor, Senator Ibikunle Amosun, has praised the people of Ondo State for “making a good choice” with the election of Chief  Rotimi Akeredolu as governor.
In a statement signed by his Senior Special Assistant on Media, Adejuwon Soyinka, Amosun said “this is one choice that will bring unprecedented progress, infrastructural development as well as social and economic growth to the sunshine state.”
Also, Minister of Mines and Steel Development, Dr. Kayode Fayemi said, yesterday, that Ondo State made the right choice in electing Akeredolu. In a congratulatory message signed by his Special Assistant on Media, Mr Yinka Oyebode, the minister said Akeredolu’s victory was victory for democracy as well as the people of Ondo State who have long clamoured for change.